Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of ensemble control and estimation, which involves the use of control inputs and measurement outputs to steer and estimate a large population of control systems. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a new class of ensemble systems and establishes conditions for controllability and observability, which involves the study of dynamical systems (cs.DS) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of Lie groups and their homogeneous spaces, which involves the study of computational engineering (cs.CE) and information theory (cs.IT).
